        fail to import with 0.4.1 scenes.<BR>&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT>=20
        <LI><FONT face=3DArial,Helvetica>v0.4.1 - Support for Editable =
Poly added.=20
        Data will be still exported as Editable Mesh but an attempt to =
convert=20
        to Editable Poly in the target application will be made. Should =
this=20
        attempt fail (for example, in 3ds max 3), the object will remain =
an=20
        Editable Mesh. <BR>Moved all import functions to the main scene =
file and=20
        made them non-optional. In the past, a mesh import function =
would be=20
        included only if a mesh has been exported, same with Spline =
import. In=20
        this version, the import functions will always be included in =
the=20
        exported scene even if not required. This is to let you =
add/remove=20
        object loading command lines from the main scene file by hand =
without=20
        getting any errors because of missing importer code.<BR>&nbsp; =
</FONT>
